author: Ashleigh Davis For Daily Mail Australia
title: Rundown Leichhardt property transformed into modern home | Daily Mail Online
text: From dump to oasis! How young Sydney woman transformed an abandoned property into a stunning inner city home for just $320,000 - and sold it for $1.4million Sydney woman Alexis Bell has transformed a rundown Leichhardt property into a modern inner city oasis She bought the Elswick Street house with her father in Sydney for $900,000 at auction in December 2015 The renovations cost $320,000 and the pair sold it for $1.4 million - making a $180,000 profit in the process Ms Bell and her father completely gutted the house and transformed it into a stylish three-bedroom home It features a spacious kitchen and living area with heated concrete floors, a bathroom with a free-standing tub, an upper-level main bedroom with an ensuite and spacious outdoor area with a wooden deck Published: 02:12 GMT, 23 February 2017 | Updated: 07:54 GMT, 23 February 2017 235 shares
